Uses of Package
fr.applicationcore.error

  • Packages that use fr.applicationcore.error 
    Package Description
    fr.applicationcore.error
    Subpackage of 'applicationcore' which contains elements to define errors and to manage those returned by the server using the ApplicationCore module for an application
    fr.applicationcore.junit.model
    Subpackage of 'applicationcore.junit' which contains elements useful to run JUnit tests
    fr.applicationcore.junit.network
    Subpackage of 'applicationcore.junit' which contains the functions to interact with the testing servers by HTTP or HTTPS protocol
    fr.applicationcore.network
    Subpackage of 'applicationcore' which contains the functions to interact by HTTP or HTTPS protocol with the server using the ApplicationCore module for an application
    fr.applicationcore.toolbox
    Subpackage of 'applicationcore' which defines the toolbox containing useful functions
    fr.junittemplate.test
    Classes necessary to test client of NodeJS servers using the Core module for an application or a service
  • Classes in fr.applicationcore.error used by fr.applicationcore.error 
    Class Description
    Error
    Description of an error returned by a NodeJS server using the ApplicationCore module for an application
    ErrorInterface
    This interface is used to process an error returned by a NodeJS server or generated by a function in the JAR when client tries to interact with an application
    ErrorMessage
    Basic attributes of an error message coming from a NodeJS server using the module entitled 'ApplicationCore'
    ErrorReferential
